## Specification Reference
- **Primary**: spec/09 title: "Performance Architecture — Columnar Storage & Zero-Copy Cold Start"
- **Supporting**: ADR-FERR-030 (wavelet matrix — operates on integer-encoded columns), NEG-FERR-007 (per-field entropy analysis)
- **Verification**: `V:PROP`, `V:TYPE`

## What
Replace `Vec<Datom>` (Array-of-Structs) in PositionalStore with per-field column arrays (Structure-of-Arrays). Each field becomes a contiguous, typed array:

```
entities:   Vec<EntityId>       // 32 bytes × N, packed
attr_ids:   Vec<AttributeId>    // 2 bytes × N (interned via bd-fnod)
values:     Vec<Value>          // ~16 bytes × N (tagged union)
tx_ids:     Vec<TxId>           // 28 bytes × N
ops:        BitVec<u64, Lsb0>   // 1 bit × N
```

## Why
The spec title says "Columnar Storage" but the implementation is AoS. This is the single largest cache utilization improvement possible.

**Cache analysis**: Scanning 100K attributes to find `:name`:
- AoS: touch 100K × ~130 bytes = 13MB. Each cache line (64 bytes) carries ~8 bytes of attribute data = **6% utilization**.
- SoA: touch 100K × 2 bytes = 200KB. Each cache line carries 32 attribute IDs = **100% utilization**.

**16x cache utilization improvement** for column scans. Fits in L2 cache (256KB) instead of requiring DRAM bandwidth.

This is THE format that prolly tree leaf chunks use in Phase 4b. Sorted columnar arrays become content-defined chunks. The Phase 4a data structure is preserved, not replaced (accretive design principle 4).

Every competing datom store (Datomic, XTDB v1, DataScript) uses AoS. XTDB v2 uses Arrow columnar but for documents, not datoms. Ferratomic's SoA is purpose-built for the 5-field datom model — no schema overhead, fixed column count, optimal for the exact access patterns the query engine uses.

## Preconditions
1. bd-fnod (attribute interning) closed — SoA attribute column requires u16 IDs.
2. PositionalStore currently stores `Vec<Datom>` as `canonical` field.

## Postconditions
1. [TYPE] PositionalStore has per-field column arrays, not Vec<Datom>. **Verify**: struct definition.
2. [EQUIV] Datom reconstruction from columns produces identical datoms. **Verify**: proptest roundtrip.
3. [SCAN] Column scan for attribute lookup touches only attr_ids array. **Verify**: benchmark.
4. [OP] Op column is BitVec (1 bit per datom, not 1 byte). **Verify**: sizeof measurement.
5. [COMPAT] All existing PositionalStore operations work on SoA layout. **Verify**: all tests pass.
6. [MERGE] merge_sort_dedup operates on SoA columns in parallel. **Verify**: merge test.
7. [PERM] Permutation arrays index into SoA by position (unchanged semantics). **Verify**: search tests.

## Pseudocode Contract

```rust
/// Structure-of-Arrays columnar store representation (spec/09 "Columnar Storage").
///
/// Each field is a contiguous array. Column scans touch only the relevant
/// field's memory, achieving 100% cache utilization vs 6% for AoS.
///
/// INV-FERR-076: positional content addressing — position i refers to the
/// datom (entities[i], attr_ids[i], values[i], tx_ids[i], ops[i]).
pub struct ColumnarStore {
    /// Entity IDs in EAVT order. 32 bytes × N, packed.
    entities: Vec<EntityId>,
    /// Interned attribute IDs (bd-fnod). 2 bytes × N.
    attr_ids: Vec<AttributeId>,
    /// Values. Tagged union, ~16 bytes × N.
    values: Vec<Value>,
    /// Transaction IDs. 28 bytes × N.
    tx_ids: Vec<TxId>,
    /// Assert/Retract. 1 BIT × N (not 1 byte).
    ops: BitVec<u64, Lsb0>,

    /// Number of datoms.
    len: usize,

    // --- Auxiliary structures (unchanged from PositionalStore) ---
    /// LIVE bitvector (INV-FERR-029).
    live_bits: SuccinctBitVec,       // bd-t84f: rank/select capable
    /// Chunk fingerprints (INV-FERR-079).
    chunk_fps: ChunkFingerprints,    // bd-0zfw
    /// Store fingerprint (INV-FERR-074).
    fingerprint: [u8; 32],
    /// Entity Bloom filter (INV-FERR-027).
    bloom: EntityBloom,
    /// CHD perfect hash (INV-FERR-027).
    entity_mph: OnceLock<Chd>,
    /// Permutation arrays (INV-FERR-073, OnceLock = lazy).
    perm_aevt: OnceLock<Vec<u32>>,
    perm_vaet: OnceLock<Vec<u32>>,
    perm_avet: OnceLock<Vec<u32>>,
}

impl ColumnarStore {
    /// Reconstruct a datom at position i. O(1).
    #[inline]
    pub fn datom_at(&self, i: usize) -> Datom {
        Datom::new(
            self.entities[i],
            intern.resolve(self.attr_ids[i]),  // u16 → &str → Attribute
            self.values[i].clone(),
            self.tx_ids[i],
            if self.ops[i] { Op::Assert } else { Op::Retract },
        )
    }

    /// Iterate only the entity column (e.g., for entity existence check).
    /// Touches 32N bytes instead of 130N.
    pub fn entity_column(&self) -> &[EntityId] { &self.entities }

    /// Iterate only the attribute column (e.g., for schema queries).
    /// Touches 2N bytes instead of 130N.
    pub fn attr_column(&self) -> &[AttributeId] { &self.attr_ids }
}
```

