## Design Decision: New dedicated HLC model

None of the existing Stateright models deal with clock behavior. HLC monotonicity requires modeling: a wall clock that can advance, stall, or regress (NTP correction), and an HLC that maintains monotonic TxId output regardless. This is a pure clock-logic model — no store, no transactions, no indexes.

The model has a small bounded state: wall_clock ∈ {0, 1, 2}, prev_physical ∈ {0, 1, 2}, prev_logical ∈ {0, 1, 2}. Actions: wall_clock_advance, wall_clock_stall (return same value), wall_clock_regress (decrease by 1), tick (apply HLC algorithm). The property: after every tick, the new (physical, logical) pair is strictly greater than the previous pair in lexicographic order.

