## Resolved Type Decisions
1. LIVE-first is FILE LAYOUT only. In-memory PositionalStore is ALWAYS EAVT-sorted.
2. Distinguish from standard V3 via version field: 0x0003 = standard V3, 0x0103 = LIVE-first V3.
3. Two-struct serialization (matching bd-a2vf): V3LiveFirstPayloadWrite (Vec<Datom>) / V3LiveFirstPayloadRead (Vec<WireDatom>). ADR-FERR-010 trust boundary.
4. LIVE and HISTORICAL datoms are SEPARATE fields in the payload. Single bincode call deserializes the struct containing both fields. "Partial" loading means: deserialize full payload, build Store from live_datoms only, RETAIN hist_datoms for later merge.
5. Full load: deserialize payload, merge-sort live+hist into EAVT canonical, build Store.
6. PartialStore holds: Store (LIVE-only) + retained hist_datoms Vec for load_historical().

