MMPH: O(1) entity→position lookup via inline CHD. Constant time regardless of scale.

| Scale | Interpolation search (bd-u6bq) | CHD MMPH | Space overhead |
|-------|-------------------------------|----------|----------------|
| 200K | ~20ns | ~25ns (2 lookups + verify) | ~75KB |
| 100M | ~400ns | ~25ns | ~37.5MB |

## Design Decision: Trait interface + inline CHD default
The Mph struct wraps a trait object so the backend can be swapped without changing any caller. Phase 4a ships inline CHD (~150 lines safe Rust). Future: swap to an external crate by implementing the trait — ONE file change, ZERO caller changes. Same abstraction pattern as perm_layout.rs (Eytzinger with vEB-ready swap).

Zero unsafe. Zero new dependencies. Full proptest + Kani coverage. EntityId-native (BLAKE3 bytes as h1/h2).

## Pseudocode — MphBackend trait (in mph.rs)

```rust
//! Monotone Minimal Perfect Hash for entity lookups (bd-wa5p).
//!
//! Architecture: MphBackend trait defines the interface. ChdBackend is the
//! Phase 4a implementation (~150 lines safe Rust). To swap to an external
//! crate: implement MphBackend for a wrapper struct, change Mph::build()
//! to construct the new backend. ZERO caller changes — callers use Mph,
//! not the backend directly.

use ferratom::EntityId;

/// Backend trait for minimal perfect hash implementations (INV-FERR-027).
///
/// Implementors map a known set of EntityIds to slots [0..n).
/// The contract:
/// - build() succeeds for uniformly distributed BLAKE3 keys (with overwhelming probability)
/// - For every key k in the construction set: lookup(k) returns a unique slot in [0..n)
/// - For keys NOT in the construction set: lookup returns an ARBITRARY slot (caller must verify)
/// - lookup is O(1)
///
/// To swap backends: implement this trait for your crate's type, then change
/// Mph::build() to construct it instead of ChdBackend. Nothing else changes.
pub(crate) trait MphBackend: Clone + std::fmt::Debug {
    /// Build from sorted unique EntityIds. Returns None on failure.
    fn build(sorted_keys: &[EntityId]) -> Option<Self> where Self: Sized;
    /// O(1) lookup: key → slot index.
    fn lookup(&self, key: &EntityId) -> usize;
    /// Number of slots.
    fn num_slots(&self) -> usize;
}
```

## Pseudocode — ChdBackend (inline CHD, ~120 lines)

```rust
/// CHD (Compress Hash Displace) backend (Belazzougui et al. 2009).
/// ~120 lines of safe Rust. Zero unsafe. Zero external dependencies.
/// Uses EntityId BLAKE3 bytes directly: bytes[0..8] as h1, bytes[8..16] as h2.
#[derive(Clone, Debug)]
pub(crate) struct ChdBackend {
    displacements: Vec<u32>,     // one per bucket
    slot_to_key_idx: Vec<u32>,   // slot → index in sorted keys array (for Mph verify)
    num_buckets: usize,
    num_slots: usize,
}

const BUCKET_RATIO: usize = 4;
const MAX_DISPLACEMENT: u32 = 1024;

fn h1(eid: &EntityId) -> u64 {
    let b = eid.as_bytes();
    u64::from_be_bytes([b[0], b[1], b[2], b[3], b[4], b[5], b[6], b[7]])
}

fn h2(eid: &EntityId) -> u64 {
    let b = eid.as_bytes();
    u64::from_be_bytes([b[8], b[9], b[10], b[11], b[12], b[13], b[14], b[15]])
}

impl MphBackend for ChdBackend {
    fn build(sorted_keys: &[EntityId]) -> Option<Self> {
        let n = sorted_keys.len();
        if n == 0 {
            return Some(Self { displacements: Vec::new(), slot_to_key_idx: Vec::new(),
                num_buckets: 0, num_slots: 0 });
        }
        let num_buckets = n / BUCKET_RATIO + 1;
        let num_slots = n;

        // Step 1: assign keys to buckets via h1
        let mut buckets: Vec<Vec<usize>> = vec![Vec::new(); num_buckets];
        for (i, key) in sorted_keys.iter().enumerate() {
            buckets[(h1(key) as usize) % num_buckets].push(i);
        }

        // Step 2: sort buckets by size (largest first)
        let mut bucket_order: Vec<usize> = (0..num_buckets).collect();
        bucket_order.sort_unstable_by(|&a, &b| buckets[b].len().cmp(&buckets[a].len()));

        // Step 3: greedy displacement assignment
        let mut displacements = vec![0u32; num_buckets];
        let mut slot_occupied = vec![false; num_slots];
        let mut slot_to_key_idx = vec![u32::MAX; num_slots];

        for &bucket_idx in &bucket_order {
            if buckets[bucket_idx].is_empty() { continue; }
            let mut found = false;
            for d in 0..MAX_DISPLACEMENT {
                let mut slots_used: Vec<usize> = Vec::with_capacity(buckets[bucket_idx].len());
                let mut collision = false;
                for &key_idx in &buckets[bucket_idx] {
                    let slot = (h2(&sorted_keys[key_idx]).wrapping_add(u64::from(d)) as usize) % num_slots;
                    if slot_occupied[slot] || slots_used.contains(&slot) {
                        collision = true;
                        break;
                    }
                    slots_used.push(slot);
                }
                if !collision {
                    displacements[bucket_idx] = d;
                    for (i, &slot) in slots_used.iter().enumerate() {
                        slot_occupied[slot] = true;
                        slot_to_key_idx[slot] = u32::try_from(buckets[bucket_idx][i])
                            .unwrap_or(u32::MAX);
                    }
                    found = true;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if !found { return None; } // extremely unlikely for BLAKE3 keys
        }
        Some(Self { displacements, slot_to_key_idx, num_buckets, num_slots })
    }

    fn lookup(&self, key: &EntityId) -> usize {
        if self.num_slots == 0 { return 0; }
        let bucket = (h1(key) as usize) % self.num_buckets;
        let d = u64::from(self.displacements[bucket]);
        (h2(key).wrapping_add(d) as usize) % self.num_slots
    }

    fn num_slots(&self) -> usize { self.num_slots }
}

impl ChdBackend {
    /// Verify that a slot corresponds to the expected key index.
    /// O(1) via reverse mapping table.
    pub(crate) fn verify_slot(&self, slot: usize, key_idx: usize) -> bool {
        slot < self.slot_to_key_idx.len()
            && self.slot_to_key_idx[slot] == u32::try_from(key_idx).unwrap_or(u32::MAX)
    }
}
```

## Pseudocode — Mph wrapper (public API, backend-agnostic)

```rust
/// Monotone Minimal Perfect Hash over EntityIds (INV-FERR-027).
///
/// Wraps an MphBackend implementation + the sorted key set for verification.
/// Callers use Mph, never the backend directly. Swapping backends changes
/// Mph::build() only — all callers are unchanged.
#[derive(Clone, Debug)]
pub(crate) struct Mph {
    /// The MPH backend (Phase 4a: ChdBackend).
    backend: ChdBackend, // Change to: Box<dyn MphBackend> if runtime polymorphism needed,
                         // OR swap ChdBackend for ExternalCrateBackend here.
    /// Sorted unique EntityIds for verify-after-lookup.
    keys: Vec<EntityId>,
}

impl Mph {
    /// Build from sorted unique EntityIds.
    /// Phase 4a: constructs ChdBackend.
    /// To swap: change ChdBackend::build to NewBackend::build here. Nothing else.
    pub(crate) fn build(sorted_keys: Vec<EntityId>) -> Option<Self> {
        let backend = ChdBackend::build(&sorted_keys)?;
        Some(Self { backend, keys: sorted_keys })
    }

    /// O(1) existence check: is this EntityId in the construction set?
    /// Returns true if present, false if absent. Zero false negatives.
    /// Uses backend lookup + key verification (not binary search).
    pub(crate) fn contains(&self, key: &EntityId) -> bool {
        if self.keys.is_empty() { return false; }
        let slot = self.backend.lookup(key);
        let key_idx = self.backend.slot_to_key_idx.get(slot).copied().unwrap_or(u32::MAX) as usize;
        key_idx < self.keys.len() && self.keys[key_idx] == *key
    }

    /// O(1) lookup: EntityId → index in the sorted unique key array.
    /// Returns None if key is absent.
    pub(crate) fn lookup_key_index(&self, key: &EntityId) -> Option<usize> {
        if self.keys.is_empty() { return None; }
        let slot = self.backend.lookup(key);
        let key_idx = self.backend.slot_to_key_idx.get(slot).copied().unwrap_or(u32::MAX) as usize;
        if key_idx < self.keys.len() && self.keys[key_idx] == *key {
            Some(key_idx)
        } else {
            None
        }
    }
}
```

