```
## Change: Add polar quantization pre-filter for EAVT
- Ordering preserved:     YES — the polar pre-filter returns candidate positions; the second stage confirms the exact match via full byte equality. The final result is the same Datom that interpolation_search would return.
- Tie-breaking unchanged: YES — same EavtKey comparator on the same canonical array.
- Floating-point:         The rotation uses f32 arithmetic. The angle quantization is a deterministic discretization (4 bits per angle). Different CPU rounding modes can produce slightly different polar surrogates ON THE BOUNDARIES — but the bounded-distortion theorem guarantees that any genuinely matching pair has identical polar surrogates regardless of rounding. The pre-filter may have more false positives on different CPUs, but never false negatives. The final equality check is integer-exact.
- RNG seeds:              N/A — rotation matrix is a compile-time const.
- Set semantics:          N/A — eavt_get returns Option<&Datom>, not a set.
- Golden outputs:         The 100K-sample bd-snnh EAVT query result hashes must be byte-identical with polar ON vs OFF.
- Edge cases verified:    empty canonical, single-element, all-equal-prefix entities, key-not-present, key-at-boundary.
